  <span id="freeText11715935034034415677" style="display:none">Hometown Girl At Heart by Kirsten Fullmer<br />This story starts out with Tara and she's won the bid to renovate the building. It's a total disaster but that never stopped her.<br />She learns of a development for the resort that will be onsite and the problem with that is she finds him very attractive and it does funny things to her stomach.<br />Story also follows Justin and he likes to do things by a certain order. He has a hard time locating TJ and the town residents are very vague til he finds a record at the town hall.<br />They had gotten off on the wrong foot to say the least.<br />Really like this story because it explains how Tara does things her way-love the recycling or products she scavengers for-so cool! Like hearing how Justin does things his way, methodical and he finds something about Tara that attracts him to her.<br />Adult scenes are included. Love how the whole town shows up for the ribbon cutting and how fast things go. Justin learns the truth about Tara over time as to how she came to be in the town and does her work and why.<br />So patriotic and caring and he's like the total opposite. Can't wait to read more from this author.<br />Received this review copy from the publicist and this is my honest opinion.<br /> </span>
