  <span id="freeText16226047260593291978" style="display:none">This was a perfect easy read to pass the days during what seemed to be a never ending lockdown. Lighthearted and doesnâ€™t take itself too seriously. Classic city boy meets (not quite country) girl storyâ€¦they donâ€™t hit it off right away but very soon they realise they share similarities where it matters and are both striving towards the same goal for very different reasons. I appreciated that Justin seemed to fall harder for Tara (or Tara wouldnâ€™t allow herself to fall for him so quickly) and he had to work a little to win her over. The story was complex and the characters had depth which is often missing from this genre. It was definitely more of a romance than erotic fiction but some scenes were still very heated. I find it difficult not to skim read to the â€˜good bitsâ€™ when reading this kind of book but the plot line and character development was enough to keep me interested even when no sex was happening. The descriptive way in which the author writes about the charactersâ€™ physical appearances paved the way for the attraction to grow from the moment Justin saw Taraâ€¦<br /><br />â€™a young woman with long, tan legsâ€¦.She wore cut off shorts and a sweaty tank top that clung provocatively to every curve of her long lean body.â€™<br /><br />â€¦and that was by page 7! No spoilers in this review but there is a well thought out plot twist and a cliffhanger at the end (this is part one of a six part series) so be prepared to buy the next book if youâ€™re the type of reader who gets invested in a story. On the plus side, it means I wasnâ€™t too disappointed when the book ended as I had the next one available to start straight away. All in all a great way to get lost for a day or three, depending on how fast you read. A romance with just the right amount of heat. </span>
