<span id="freeTextContainer4999034309810213663">Loved this book. I kept reading Tara&apos;s name as Tura since that&apos;s my name. I loved Tara and how caring and determined, and how strong-willed and hard-headed she was. I love how she and Justin work together and how they start out annoying the crap out of each other and end up falling in love. I expected that to happen naturally but it was super sweet to read. I loved how Tara had to renovate and fix up the old house before she sold it. I loved the romance and thought this was a great book. I give </span>
  <span id="freeText4999034309810213663" style="display:none">Loved this book. I kept reading Tara's name as Tura since that's my name. I loved Tara and how caring and determined, and how strong-willed and hard-headed she was. I love how she and Justin work together and how they start out annoying the crap out of each other and end up falling in love. I expected that to happen naturally but it was super sweet to read. I loved how Tara had to renovate and fix up the old house before she sold it. I loved the romance and thought this was a great book. I give this book 5 stars. </span>
